REST Assured
> REST Assured is a Java package for testing REST APIs.
> REST Assured provides a fluent syntax (and not a DSL) for writing service calls directly in Java code.
> The fluent syntax is based on Gherkin:
    > given() a request spec is created,
    > when() the call is made,
    > then() verify the response.
Although REST Assured is not a full testing framework, it nevertheless pulls inspiration from BDD frameworks for order and structure.

